{
  "text": "As shown in Fig. 1D , only anti-sense strands of PCR products (shown as the filled rectangles with white dots) labeled with biotin (shown as the asterisks) were used for hybridization against sensestrand probes (shown as the dotted rectangles) tiled on the chip. In addition, for each tag, four priming sequences were shielded by blocking oligonucleotides (shown as rectangles in gray; refer to the previous report [CITATION_1] for the sequence information), which prevented melted strands from re-associating.",
  "correct_citation": {
